FlyNetSim Jamming / Channel-Hopping Defense Testbed
===================================================

This repository accompanies the paper:

  "A Reproducible Co-Simulation Testbed for UAV Wi-Fi Jamming and
   Channel-Hopping Defense", IEEE CCNC 2027 (Testbed Track).
  Authors: Rajarshi Sen [+ co-authors: TODO], Florida Institute of Technology.

It is licensed under the GNU General Public License v2 (see LICENSE), consistent
with ns-3, on which the network simulation is built.


Provenance of the files
-----------------------

This work extends FlyNetSim:

  Baidya, S., Shaikh, Z., Levorato, M. "FlyNetSim: An Open Source Synchronized
  UAV Network Simulator based on ns-3 and Ardupilot." Proc. ACM MSWiM, 2018,
  pp. 37-45.  https://github.com/saburhb/FlyNetSim

  @inproceedings{baidya2018flynetsim,
    title={FlyNetSim: An Open Source Synchronized UAV Network Simulator based on
           ns-3 and Ardupilot},
    author={Baidya, Sabur and Shaikh, Zoheb and Levorato, Marco},
    booktitle={Proceedings of the 21st ACM International Conference on Modeling,
               Analysis and Simulation of Wireless and Mobile Systems},
    pages={37--45}, year={2018}, organization={ACM}
  }

New in this work (original contributions, (C) the authors):
  - bridge/mavlink_zmq_bridge.py         four-thread MAVLink<->ZMQ bridge (replaces
                                         FlyNetSim's Python 2 / DroneKit / PyQt4 stack)
  - the channel-hopping defense inside ns3/scratch/flynetsim/uav-net-sim.cc
    (CheckJamming / DoChannelHop / ReadThreshold), the TCP stream reassembly,
    and the per-lane packet scheduling
  - ns3/patches/mac-low-hop-assert.patch  hop-assertion clamp for ns-3.27
  - scripts/ (setup.sh, master_parser.py, make_figures.py) and env/ (Dockerfile,
    requirements.txt)

Reused from FlyNetSim, modified (shipped here with attribution headers, GPLv2):
  - ns3/scratch/flynetsim/uav-net-sim.cc  (heavily modified: defense + reassembly added)
  - ns3/scratch/flynetsim/myApps.cc, myApps.h  (small additions for defense counters)
  - ns3/scratch/flynetsim/wscript         (standard ns-3 scratch build file)
  - ns3/scratch/flynetsim/config.example.xml  (extended with the <threshold> field)

Reused from FlyNetSim, VERBATIM (NOT re-hosted here — fetched from the upstream
repository by scripts/setup.sh at build time):
  - myInput.cc, myInput.h
  - FlyNetSim's ns-3 patches (wscript.patch, packet-sink.h.patch)

Third-party components (fetched, not included):
  - ns-3.27          GNU GPL v2                 https://www.nsnam.org
  - ArduPilot        GNU GPL v3, pinned at tag Copter-4.0.0
                     (commit 49693540bd555a44d30fc33366b1b8a24977e429)
                     https://github.com/ArduPilot/ardupilot
  - QGroundControl   runs on the host, not distributed here

Redistribution note: the original FlyNetSim repository carries no explicit license.
The reused files link ns-3 (GPL v2) and are treated as GPL v2 here, with full
attribution above. Verbatim FlyNetSim files are fetched from the upstream
repository rather than re-hosted.
